article.description: Ray Salnave had 16 points and eight rebounds as Monmouth beat Manhattan 65-58 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Salnave lifts Monmouth over Manhattan 65-58
article.story: NEW YORK -- Ray Salnave had 16 points and eight rebounds as Monmouth beat Manhattan 65-58 on Saturday night. Deion Hammond had 16 points for Monmouth (10-7, 4-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Marcus McClary added 13 points and six rebounds. George Papas had six rebounds. Elijah Buchanan had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Jaspers (8-7, 4-2). Warren Williams added 12 points. Tykei Greene, the Jaspers' leading scorer entering the matchup at 12 points per game, failed to make a shot from the field (0 of 5). Monmouth takes on Niagara at home on Friday. Manhattan takes on Marist on the road on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
